## PAGE STRUCTURE RULES

### Every page must have:
1. Navbar (sticky, white)
2. PageHero (dark navy, Cormorant headline, red CTAs)
3. Eyebrow label above every section headline (12px, uppercase, red, letter-spacing 0.1em)
4. CTABlock at bottom (dark navy, phone + form)
5. Footer (two-tone: cream top, dark bottom)
6. Mobile sticky bar

### Homepage sections (in order):
1. Hero — navy, headline, 2 CTAs, hero image, Google badge
2. The Arcadia Difference — 3 pillars (Clinical / Guided / Dignity)
3. Services Grid — 6 featured cards
4. How Care Starts — 3 steps with images
5. Conditions Cloud — pill tags on navy background
6. Testimonials — rotating carousel
7. Referral Section — for professionals
8. Locations — 5 region tiles
9. CTA / Contact — phone + form
10. Footer

---

## CONVERSION RULES

**Phone first.** Every page, every scroll position — the phone number must be visible or one tap away.

- Desktop: phone in navbar always visible
- Mobile: sticky bottom bar, left button = call (red bg)
- Hero: phone CTA is the PRIMARY button (bigger, red, left)
- CTABlock: phone number displayed at 22px+ bold

**Form = secondary.** Short, 4 fields max: Name, Phone, Email, Message.  
Label: "Book a Free Consultation" — never "Contact Us" or "Submit".

**Referral pathway is separate.** Never mix family CTA with referral CTA.  
Referral link: in nav, in footer, in dedicated section on homepage.

---

## SEO RULES

### Meta pattern
```
Title:       [Page Topic] | Arcadia Home Care | [City if applicable]
Description: 150–160 chars, include primary keyword + soft CTA
Canonical:   https://arcadiahomecare.ca/[path]/
```

### Schema required on every page
- Homepage: Organization + AggregateRating
- Service pages: Service schema + BreadcrumbList
- Condition pages: MedicalCondition + BreadcrumbList + FAQPage
- Location pages: LocalBusiness with areaServed + BreadcrumbList
- Guide pages: Article + BreadcrumbList

### Internal linking
- Every service page → 2-3 condition pages + 2-3 guides + 1 location page
- Every condition page → 2-3 service pages + 2-3 guides
- Every guide → 1 service + 1 condition + CTABlock
- Every location page → service hub + dementia service + contact

---

## COPY VOICE & TONE

- Warm but authoritative — never cold, never salesy
- Lead with empathy, follow with expertise
- Short sentences. Active voice. No jargon.
- Always speak to the emotional state: overwhelmed, guilty, exhausted, hopeful
- "We" refers to Arcadia. "You" refers to the family member reading.
- Never say "submit" — say "book", "start", "connect"
- Never say "click here" — use action-oriented anchor text

**Headline formula:** [Emotional truth] + [Clinical credibility]  
Example: "Care That Understands What Your Family Is Going Through"

**CTA formula:** Action + Value  
Example: "Book a Free Consultation" / "Call Us — No Obligation"

---

## AUDIENCE RULES

### Primary: Adult Children (45–65)
- Emotional state: overwhelmed, guilty, time-poor, scared
- Want to feel: reassured, guided, not alone
- Speak to: safety, dignity, process clarity, caregiver quality
- Decision trigger: fall, diagnosis, hospital discharge, burnout

### Secondary: Referring Professionals
- Hospital discharge planners, social workers, OTs, geriatricians
- Want: reliable partner for complex cases, clear communication
- Speak to: clinical competence, coordination, responsiveness
- Pathway: dedicated Referral Form — never mixed with family CTAs

---

## ACCESSIBILITY

- All images require descriptive alt text
- Minimum color contrast: 4.5:1 for body text
- Focus states visible on all interactive elements
- Minimum font size: 16px body
- Tap targets: minimum 44×44px on mobile
- Lazy load all images below fold

---

## TECH STACK

- Next.js 14, App Router
- `output: 'export'` — static files for SiteGround
- `trailingSlash: true`
- Tailwind CSS + inline styles for component-specific overrides
- Google Fonts: Cormorant Garamond + DM Sans
- Images: unoptimized (required for static export)
- Forms: Formspree or SiteGround PHP handler
- Analytics: GA4 (add ID when available)
- Facebook Pixel: ID `1719807932099643` (already wired in layout)

---

## WHAT TO AVOID

- ❌ Generic "AI slop" aesthetics — no purple gradients, no Inter font, no cookie-cutter layouts
- ❌ Flat white pages with no visual hierarchy
- ❌ Cards without descriptions — always include icon + title + body + CTA
- ❌ "Submit" buttons
- ❌ Mixing referral and family CTAs on the same component
- ❌ Dark logo on dark background
- ❌ Missing eyebrow labels on sections
- ❌ Forms with more than 4–5 fields (except dedicated referral form)
- ❌ Pages without a CTABlock at the bottom
- ❌ Missing schema markup on service/condition/location pages
- ❌ Placeholder lorem ipsum copy — always write real, on-brand copy

